title: Fix off-by-one for Nuremberg fix.
message:
Fix off-by-one for Nuremberg fix.

The limit in string.split() introduced by commit
8dfbc947d19c960b4200ec88f555ee187962a540
triggers an array out of bounds exception. Also since we want the second
result, the limit is wrong anyway. The date given has the form
(DD.MM.YYYY - DD.MM.YYYY) with the start and end date of the lending
period. For the account listing the second date is the relevant one.

title: Updated reminder feature
message:
Updated reminder feature

* Create ReminderCheckService and new notification system

* Refactor account item data format
- New classes LentItem and ReservedItem
- use Joda Time LocalDate for dates without time information instead of timestamps

* Fixes and improvements for ReminderCheckService and notifications
including:
- open AccountFragment with the correct account when clicking on notifications
- update alarms after settings changes
- add ability to "snooze" notifications
- reschedule alarms after reboot
- clear alarms after clicking on "clear cache"
- warning period selection in days instead of milliseconds
- ...

* Update "notification_warning" value after updating app

* Generate alarms inside the app

* SyncAccountService: Change sync period depending on if last sync failed

* Bugfixes for reminder service

* Adapt tests to new Account data structure

* Fix API errors

* Settings: Add warning about notifications without WiFi

* Re-show notifications e.g. after reboot or app update

* SyncAccountService: Don't do anything if notifications are disabled

* Improve behavior after settings changes

* Resolve Android Studio warnings

title: Allow custom SSL certificates
message:
Allow custom SSL certificates

Some libraries have SSL certificates which are not recognized trusted by Android (or, sometimes only as of Android 3.x/4.x). We do want to use them anyways. Don't want to allow all certificates or turn off hostname validation, just specific ones we ship in our BKS keystore. This is not less secure than what we have now, because we for now trust not more than two certificates more than before -- and those two were verified (and can only be used for this specific library, due to the domain name they are limited to).

fixing #156 and #91
